Class JFXDrawer

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.Parent
        • javafx.scene.layout.Region
          • javafx.scene.layout.Pane

              • com.jfoenix.controls.JFXDrawer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget

    public class JFXDrawer
extends javafx.scene.layout.StackPane
    JFXDrawer is material design implementation of drawer. the drawer has two main nodes, the content and side pane.
    • content pane: is a stack pane that holds the nodes inside the drawer
    • side pane: is a stack pane that holds the nodes inside the drawer side area (Drawable node)
    Since:
    2016-03-09

      • isOpened

        public boolean isOpened()
        This indicates whether or not the drawer is completely shown.
        Returns:
        True if the drawer is totally visible and not transitioning, otherwise false.

      • isOpening

        public boolean isOpening()
        This indicates whether or not the drawer is in the process of being shown.
        Returns:
        True if the drawer is transitioning from closed to open, otherwise false.

      • isClosing

        public boolean isClosing()
        This indicates whether or not the drawer is in the process of being hidden.
        Returns:
        True if the drawer is transitioning from open to closed, otherwise false.

      • isClosed

        public boolean isClosed()
        This indicates whether or not the drawer is completely hidden.
        Returns:
        True if the drawer is hidden and not in the process of transitioning, otherwise false.

      • toggle

        public void toggle()
        Toggles the drawer between open and closed. The drawer will be closed if it is shown or transitioning between closed and open. Likewise, it will be opened if it is open or transitioning from open to closed.

      • open

        public void open()
        Starts the animation to transition this drawer to open.

      • close

        public void close()
        Starts the animation to transition this drawer to closed.
